In MSTest v4, `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(object, out T)` had the `out` parameter overload removed. The replacement is `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(object)` which now returns the typed value directly.

So:
```csharp
// MSTest v3
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<FastProcessor>(processor, out var typed);

// MSTest v4
var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<FastProcessor>(processor);
```

Let me fix all three test methods. Also, the csproj still shows MSTest 3.8.0 — the user says they're upgrading to 4.x, so I should update that too.


I'll start by updating the project file to reference MSTest 4.x, then refactor each assertion to use the new return-based API.

